This license is a source-available, fair-code style license. It is not an
OSI-approved open-source license. It is intended to allow internal self-hosting,
evaluation, learning, contribution, and internal modification while reserving
commercial resale, hosted resale, white-label, OEM, and competing redistribution
rights for a separate commercial license.

This draft must be approved by the project maintainer before publication. It is
not a statement of external legal approval.

1. Definitions

"Software" means the E-Office source code, documentation, packages, examples,
and related materials distributed with this license.

"Internal Business Use" means installing, running, evaluating, testing,
modifying, and using the Software for your own internal operations, internal
business workflows, internal users, or non-commercial personal use. Internal
Business Use does not include offering access to the Software to third parties
as a hosted service, managed service, white-label product, OEM component, or
commercially redistributed product.

"Commercial Hosting" means providing third parties with paid or monetized
access to the Software, or to a service substantially based on the Software,
where you operate, host, administer, or control the environment.

"Managed Service" means operating, administering, maintaining, or supporting an
instance of the Software for a third party in a way that effectively gives that
third party access to the Software as the product or a substantial part of the
product.

"White-Label" means presenting the Software, or a service substantially based
on it, under another name, brand, logo, domain, or identity in a way that hides
or replaces E-Office as the source technology.

"OEM / Embedded Distribution" means bundling, embedding, integrating, or
including the Software or a derivative work in another product, appliance,
platform, package, or service distributed or sold to third parties.

"Redistribution" means making copies of the Software or derivative works
available to third parties, whether modified or unmodified, including by source
code, binary, container image, hosted download, marketplace listing, package
registry, or similar channel.

"Commercial License" means a separate written agreement with the copyright
holder or an authorized maintainer that grants rights beyond this Community
Source License.

2. Rights granted without a Commercial License

Subject to this license, you may:

- view, study, and evaluate the Software;
- install and run the Software for Internal Business Use;
- modify the Software for Internal Business Use;
- use the Software for development, testing, and non-commercial personal use;
- create contributions and submit them to the project;
- provide consulting, implementation, training, integration, migration, or
  support services around the Software, provided those services do not amount
  to Commercial Hosting, a Managed Service, White-Label resale, OEM / Embedded
  Distribution, or commercial Redistribution of the Software itself.

3. Rights that require a Commercial License

You must obtain a Commercial License before you:

- offer paid hosted access to the Software or to a service substantially based
  on the Software;
- provide the Software as SaaS, Commercial Hosting, a service bureau, or a
  Managed Service to third parties;
- White-Label, resell, or rebrand the Software or a service substantially based
  on it;
- distribute modified or unmodified copies commercially as a competing product;
- use the Software for OEM / Embedded Distribution;
- sublicense the Software or grant third parties rights beyond this license.

